  "prompt": "What is the best camera for black and white photography?",
  "response": "There's no single \"best\" camera for black and white photography, but some great options include:\n\n1. Leica Monochrom\n- Specifically designed for black and white photography\n- Full-frame sensor\n- Exceptional image quality\n- Very expensive\n\n2. Fujifilm X-T series\n- Great JPG black and white film simulations\n- Lightweight and versatile\n- More affordable\n\n3. Pentax K-1\n- Excellent in-camera black and white filters\n- Full-frame DSLR\n- Good dynamic range\n\n4. Sony A7 series\n- High-resolution full-frame mirrorless cameras\n- Excellent low-light performance\n- Can be converted to dedicated black and white\n\n5. Film Cameras\n- Vintage Leica rangefinders\n- Hasselblad medium format cameras\n- Nikon FM2 or F series\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" camera depends on:\n- Your budget\n- Preferred shooting style\n- Technical requirements\n- Personal preference\n\nMany photographers recommend focusing more on technique, lighting, and composition than on specific camera equipment.",
